	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Ahh, old Beagle Bros material... *sheds a tear from his early Apple II days*<br /><br />The reference I've used for over 2 decades is the <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/images/7/76/Programmanual.pdf" class="postlink">Programming the 65816 (including the 6502, 65C02, and 65802)</a> book by Western Design Center / Ron Lichty / David Eyes.  See Chapter 19 for charts, and Chapter 18 for in-depth details of each opcode behaviour.  The important thing to remember when using this, however, is that it's mainly intended for 65816 -- but the 6502 and 65c02 details are there, so as long as you read the correct column / understand what it is you're looking at, you're fine.<br /><br />Matter of what works for each person, but I cannot stand &quot;posters&quot;.  I cannot deal with getting up from my desk to go stare at something extremely tacky on my wall.  I'd rather have paper in book or three-ring-binder form in front of me, or in digital form (where hopefully the PDF is actual text and not page after page of JPEG images).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


